Streets, lamposts, complex victorian architecture
---
People walking by, drenched in last night's rain. Fog, thick fog devouring the souls of fleeting happiness. There's nothing to find on these streets.
---

commands_raw:
This place is no better, broken timber walls, creeked stairwells that has certainly seen better days. Candlelights are smelting by the worthless tiny flames burning on top of their stalk. 
---
The air hangs heavy with mildew and old regret. Wallpaper peels like skin from bone, revealing strange markings etched directly into the foundation. Perhaps they're runes, or scratches, or something that wanted out.
---
